gov.nasa.arc.mct.evaluator.api
Interface Evaluator

All Superinterfaces:
Executor
public interface Evaluator
extends Executor

The evaluator interface is implemented by classes providing evaluation capabilities based on telemetry values. This interface is designed to provide a language and execution agnostic interface, so it supports multiple languages. This interface is obtained through the AbstractComponent.getCapability(Class) method and thus the absence of an evaluator must be considered in client code. The evaluation infrastructure is currently being developed, so this interface is subject to change.

requiresMultipleInputs

boolean requiresMultipleInputs()
Determines if the evaluator requires multiple inputs (which are specified by the child relationships). If this method returns false, each child in the child relationships represents one input that can be evaluated.

Specified by:
requiresMultipleInputs in interface Executor
Returns:
true if all the children need to be used for evaluation or false if only one child needs to be used as input
